Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setSdpObjectStatus(25.10)                            setSdpObjectStatus(25.10)

Name
       setSdpObjectStatus  - Sets the placement status of all or specified SDP
       group/instances

Syntax
       setSdpObjectStatus

       [-help]

       -status {unplaced|placed|fixed|cover}

       [-name object_name_list | -all]

       Sets the placement status of all or specified SDP group/instances. With
       setSdpObjectStatus, you can make the placer move  or  prevent  it  from
       moving to adjust placement of SDP elements. For example, if you specify
       status  as  unplaced,  the command unplaces the data path and moves its
       boundary outside the die area on the right hand side.

       Use this command after placement to set SDP status to  fixed  so  other
       applications  will preserve SDP placement (don't touch). Use the setSd-
       pObjectStatus command before running optimization to set SDP  placement
       status to placed so optDesign can further resize instances of SDP.

       Before setting object status with setSdpObjectStatus, you should have:

              * Imported the design

              * Defined the SDP group or instance

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each setSdpObjectStatus parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man setSdpObjectStatus.

       -all   Changes the placement status of all members of all SDP groups.

              Note: If neither -all nor -name is specified, setSdpObjectStatus
              changes placement status of all SDPs.

       -name <object_name_list>
              Specifies the names of SDP groups or instances  whose  placement
              status needs to change.

       -status {unplaced|placed|fixed|cover}
              Specifies the new placement status.

Examples
       The   following  command  changes  the  placement  status  of  all  SDP
       groups/instances to placed:

       setSdpObjectStatus -status placed

